e { mem::transmute::<*const dyn Trait, raw::TraitObject>(ptr::null::<Struct>()).vtable };\r\n```\r\n\r\nI expected to see this happen: \r\nI get the vtable as a const.\r\n\r\nInstead, this happened: \r\n`error: untyped pointers are not allowed in constant`\r\n\r\n### Version it worked on\r\nProbably before c400f758e5cda9c2617f6d8dec87a6f24ddb291\r\nEdit:  added PR number #71665\r\n\r\n### Version with regression\r\nrustc 1.49.0-nightly (e160e5cb8 2020-10-14)\r\n\r\nAny chance we can get the example code to compile again?\r\nIs there a different way to get the vtable?", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/77995/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/77995/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": null}